The '''Institute of Ocean Sciences''' is operated by [[Fisheries and Oceans Canada]] and is one of the largest marine research centres in [[Canada]]. It is located on [[Patricia Bay]] and the former [[British Columbia Highway 17A]] in [[Sidney, British Columbia|Sidney]], [[British Columbia]] on [[Vancouver Island]] just west of [[Victoria International Airport]].
The institute is paired with a [[Canadian Coast Guard]] base, and makes use of the ships {{ship|CCGS|John P. Tully}} and {{ship|CCGS|Sir Wilfrid Laurier}} as well as the Japanese {{ship|RV|Mirai}}.
